    <div class="text">
      <div class="inner">
        <h3 class="title-top">Use Case</h3>
        <h2 class="title-bottom">With Rotationstopper</h2>
        <p>Using the handles the rescuer can change or stop his rotation around the vertical axis easily. </p>
        <p>Once aligned to the rock wall, he can stay in this position until he has arrived at the rock wall. Wind and pendulum movements have no influence on his position.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="prototype">
    <div class="text">
      <div class="inner">
        <h2>Prototype</h2>
        <p>In practice, it already works with a 5 € electric motor and a 500 g brass disc in my hands.  I can control my rotation on an  office chair without any ground contact.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
